                <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-secondary mb-6">Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-4">What Are Cookies?</h3>
                        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Cookies are small files that are stored on your device when you visit our website. They contain information about your browsing activity and preferences. Cookies help us remember your information, understand how you use our site, and improve your experience.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-4">Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
                        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                            We use the following types of cookies:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed ml-4">
                            <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Necessary for the website to function properly and provide services you request</li>
                            <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our website and identify areas for improvement</li>
                            <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember your preferences and settings to enhance your user experience</li>
                            <li><strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> Track your activity to deliver targeted advertising and measure campaign effectiveness</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-4">Other Tracking Technologies</h3>
                        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                            In addition to cookies, we may use other tracking technologies, including:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed ml-4">
                            <li><strong>Web Beacons:</strong> Small graphics that track page views and clicks</li>
                            <li><strong>Pixels:</strong> Tiny images used to track user behavior and conversions</li>
                            <li><strong>Analytics Tools:</strong> Services that track website usage and user behavior</li>
                            <li><strong>Advertising Networks:</strong> Third-party services that deliver targeted ads based on your interests</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-4">Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h3>
                        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can set your browser to refuse cookies or alert you when cookies are being sent. However, blocking cookies may affect your ability to use certain features of our website. You can also opt out of targeted advertising by adjusting your advertising preferences in your browser or device settings.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
